jenkinsfile: pipeline as a code

1. start jenkins 
2. Install pipeline plugin 
3. Create a new job
4. Create/ get jenkinsfile in pipeline section 
5. Check output


It can be written in 2 way delecrative way(new) and scripted way (old) uses groovy 
difference if format and structure 

if you want to add steps go to pipeline syntax and there you cann specify steps click on generate code it will generate code 

How we can get the jenkins file from Git or any SCM 


Steps 
1. create new job or use existing job(type: pipeline)
2. create a repository or github 
3. Add jenkins file in git repo
4. under jenkins job --> pipeline section --> select defination pipeline script from SCM 
5. add repo and jenkinsfile location in the job under pipeline section 
6. Save and run 

How to clone a git repo using jenkinsfile 
Add the path using pipeline syntax 
